Responsibilities:

  Responsible for daily workshop operations including handling customers’ complaints
  Monitor workshop performance and suggest initiatives for improvement
  Provide guidance and promote continuous learning such as technical training for both frontline and workshop staff
  Uphold the work culture that promotes good work attitude and teamwork, and conduct regular performance review with staff to ensure company's objectives are met
  Meeting with both external and internal stakeholders on workshop matters


Requirements:

  Degree holder preferably in Mechanical / Electrical Engineering or its equivalent with at least 3 years in the automotive industry
  Able to face challenges and meet customer’s expectation on service and quality
  Possess excellent leadership, analytical, planning, execution, problems solving skills
  Good interpersonal skills
  Strong written and presentation skills


Please write us a cover letter for us to understand why you will be keen to join us if you are not previously from automotive industry.